review_blob: this is beer gets underrated the further away from pottsville pa you get.  this is a valid gripe because the taste and feel of the beer from a fresh keg in pennsylvania is absolutely fantastic
good taste at first. i dont enjoy drinking alot of this throughout a night but it has been a great beer when ive decided to throw one back.
Great beer. great aroma, taste is the best attribute by far. can drink it all night and will doing it a again soon.

Ive a lot of fun with this beer over the years and even though Im a bit upset that they stop putting pick-up lines on the side of the bottles (mostly because its worked for me more then not), this is a good beer that goes down easy.

This is one of the highest rated beers for a reason.  Such a great taste.  Stronger then your common run-of-the-mill beer weeds out the binge drinkers.  This is not a chugging beer and should be enjoyed with no rush. 
Also, its slightly better on tap.
September and this beer go together very well. Spaten Oktoberfest in the local beer garden is the way to go. Grab a stein and cheers all night.

Tap.  Golden beer w/ a light head.  There has been a couple versions of this beer brewed already at Port 44 and theyve been very similar to each other.  The sooner you get to a fresh batch the better. Overall an EXCELLENT beer.
Its a good beer.  Love that it is un-filtered. I am looking forward to it it being perfected on the tap and eventually becoming one of my favorites.
The Red is amazing. Excellent choice of hops and malt.  I hope this beer never leaves the taps at this brewery.
Great Beer!  Excellent taste and flavor for a stronger beer.  Im not the hugest stout drinker but this is helping turn into one.
